  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Heater Unit/Core Removal and Installation"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the engine is hot, allow it to cool sufficiently before working on it.",
        "If there are components of the SRS airbag system in the vicinity, refer to the work precautions and configuration drawings described for the SRS airbag system before proceeding."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Cooling water removal",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000435",
          "label": "Cooling water removal",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Disconnect suction hose and receiver pipe",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000878",
          "label": "Disconnect suction hose and receiver pipe",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Heater hose disconnect"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "879_5.0_jpn_11580978_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Slide the clamp (A) and disconnect the inlet side heater hose (B) from the outlet side heater hose (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "As coolant flows out, use a receiving rag or similar item in a container to prevent it from adhering to the body."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "4. Remove instrument panel/steering hanger beam",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000789",
          "label": "Remove instrument panel/steering hanger beam",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "5. Blower/heater unit removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "879_5.0_jpn_11580979_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the drain hose (A). Remove the blower/heater unit (B). Remove the intake duct (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Coolant will flow out, so a vinyl sheet or similar material should be placed on the floor and a rag should be used to prevent it from sticking to the body."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "6. Heater core removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "879_5.0_jpn_11580980_5.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Remove the dust seal (A). Remove the cover (B) and remove the heater core (C)."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "7. Precautions for installation work"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "Do not mistake the heater hose for the inlet side or the outlet side.",
        "Heater hose clamps must be securely attached.",
        "The O-ring at the pipe connection must be replaced with a new one, and compressor oil (SP-10) must be applied before installation."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "8. Vacuuming/leak testing/refrigerant sealing",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R002698",
          "label": "Vacuuming/leak testing/refrigerant sealing",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "After installation, perform vacuuming, leak test, and refrigerant sealing."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "9. performance test",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000907",
          "label": "performance test",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "source": "sm_contents/60T6GD00_2014_jpn_RIN_20131205174356/Contents/jpn/60T6GD00_2014/RIN/SCT/SC/SYS/R000879_jpn/web/html/R000879_jpn_Content.html",
  "inOutline": true
}